-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/barclays-bank-sells-29-million-reais-of-discount-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:            Barclays Bank Plc.
Amount:            28.5 million Brazilian Reais
Coupon:            0.50 percent of face value
Issue Price:       77.06 percent of face value
Duration:          4 years
Sales period:      March 15 - March 28
Settlement date:   March 30, 2012
Maturity:          March 30, 2016
Uridashi Manager:  Takagi Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  